-- Predicativity: a type-constructor argument ranges over monotypes, so a
-- polymorphic type written directly as a `List` element is impredicative and
-- rejected with a clear message (wrap it in a data type to carry it first-class).
fn idlist() : List(forall a. (a) -> a) = Cons(\(x) -> x, Nil)

fn main() : Int = 0
